**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion GradedObject (I₁ × I₂) C := fun ⟨i₁, i₂⟩ => (K.X i₁).X i₂ ```

**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion (f.f i₁).f i₂ ≫ (L.d i₁ i₁').f i₂ = (K.d i₁ i₁').f i₂ ≫ (f.f i₁').f i₂ := ```
Do you think you can deduplicate these two parts?

I will try to experiment with a slightly different design: introducing two horizontal and vertical operators on `total.X` (rather than on individual summands). I do not think there is anything that could be deduplicated here and in the proof of `d_comp_d`, but it may give slightly better looking proofs.
This proof is massive. Do you think you can factor out some parts, and possibly deduplicate a bit?

Thanks for the review! In the last commit https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/commit/2f17fe7f98d8c43b1217a0a220eb901f6f45503e I have added definitions `D₁` and `D₂`, so that the differential is `d := D₁ + D₂`, and in order to prove `d_comp_d`, I have obtained separate lemmas `D₁_D₁`, `D₂_D₁` and `D₂_D₂`. The code is then slightly longer, but appears in smaller chunks; overall, it should be more manageable. (I also believe that introducing these definitions `D₁` and `D₂` will ease certain future developments.)
